FRA Frontend — What’s Done

Overview
- Built with React 18 + Vite + TypeScript
- UI framework: Tailwind CSS with shadcn/ui (Radix primitives)
- State/data: React Query, React Hook Form, Zod validation
- Routing: React Router v6 with role-based protection
- Maps: Leaflet + React-Leaflet
- Charts: Recharts
- Icons: lucide-react
- Animations: tailwindcss-animate + subtle motion (Framer Motion available)
- Notifications: shadcn/ui Toast + Sonner
- i18n: i18next + react-i18next (en, hi, te, or, bn)

Information Architecture
- Role-based landing: `RoleBasedRouter` drives which dashboard the user sees
  - government → `GovernmentDashboard`
  - ministry_tribal → `TribalDashboard`
  - welfare_dept → `WelfareDashboard`
  - forest_revenue → `ForestRevenueDashboard`
  - planning_develop → `PlanningDevelopmentDashboard`
  - ngo → `NGODashboard`
  - normal/unauthenticated → `LocalDashboard` (limited)
- Protected routes via `ProtectedRoute` enforcing `requiredRole`
- Global providers: QueryClientProvider, AuthProvider, TooltipProvider, Toasters

Design System, Look & Feel (UI/UX Theme)
- Theming strategy: CSS variables (HSL) + Tailwind tokens defined in `src/index.css` and mapped in `tailwind.config.ts`
  - Light: calm forest/earth palette (forest greens, muted earth oranges, neutral papers)
  - Dark: high-contrast grayscale adaptation
  - Key tokens: `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, `--secondary`, `--accent`, `--dashboard-*`, `--status-*`
- Dark mode: class-based (darkMode: "class"), fully themeable via CSS vars
- Spacing & radius: consistent radii via `--radius` and container paddings
- Shadows: layered depth tokens (`--shadow-card`, `--shadow-panel`, `--shadow-elevated`) for soft elevation
- Typography: defaults via Tailwind + antialiased body; language-specific accenting via `applyLanguageAccent`
- Layout chrome: fixed nav height `--nav-height` with subtle header gradient for depth without clutter
- Status/priority utility classes: `.status-*` and `.priority-*` for consistent semantic color use
- Buttons/utilities: `.btn-primary`, `.btn-secondary`, `.btn-outline`, `.btn-ghost`, `.clickable`, `.card-interactive`
- Accessibility-first
  - High-contrast foregrounds on themed backgrounds
  - Touch target utilities (`.touch-target`) and mobile text sizing rules
  - Reduced cognitive load through consistent semantics and spacing

Component Library (shadcn/ui + custom)
- shadcn/ui primitives under `src/components/ui`: accordion, alert(-dialog), avatar, badge, breadcrumb, button, calendar, card, carousel, chart, checkbox, collapsible, command, context-menu, dialog, drawer, dropdown-menu, form, hover-card, input(-otp), label, menubar, navigation-menu, pagination, popover, progress, radio-group, resizable, scroll-area, select, separator, sheet, sidebar, skeleton, slider, sonner, switch, table, tabs, textarea, toast, toaster, toggle(-group), tooltip, use-toast
- Custom feature components under `src/components`:
  - Data capture & workflows: `FRAApplicationForm`, `FRAApplicationList`, `AlertManagement`, `AlertViewer`
  - Mapping & spatial: `MapView`, `AIMapView`, `ForestLayout`, `ControlPanel`, `DetailsDrawer`
  - AI & insights: `AIAssetAnalysis`, `AIInsightsDashboard`, `AIFRAValidation`, `ChatWidget`
  - Content & UI: `Header`, `BottomNavigation`, `PhotoSlider`, `FAQSection`, `ContactSection`, `SecretShortcut`, `ProtectedRoute`, `RoleSpecificDashboard`, `Groundwater3D`

Navigation & Pages
- Top-level routes in `src/App.tsx` with `RoleBasedRouter` and fallbacks
- Pages under `src/pages`: Landing, LimitedLanding, RoleSelection, GovernmentDashboard, LocalDashboard, TribalDashboard, WelfareDashboard, ForestRevenueDashboard, PlanningDevelopmentDashboard, NGODashboard, AnalyzeDocuments, Documentation, Security, Status, Login, SignUp, NotFound
- `ChatWidget` mounted globally for contextual assistance

Maps & Geo UI
- Leaflet container styling in `index.css`: full-width, responsive, z-index layering to avoid UI overlap
- Viewport utilities: `.map-viewport`, `forest-*` layers ensure panel/map stacking order
- Control panel & drawer: responsive off-canvas patterns for tools/filters on mobile

Charts & Analytics
- Recharts for dashboards and summaries; consistent palette via theme tokens
- Progress/Status primitives using shadcn components for badges, toasts, and progress bars

Forms & Validation
- React Hook Form with Zod resolvers for robust validation UX
- Consistent inputs via shadcn `input`, `select`, `textarea`, `form` helpers
- Accessible focus states: ring/border tokens aligned with theme (`--ring`, `--border`)

Notifications & Feedback
- Dual toasters: shadcn `Toaster` and Sonner for light, transient feedback
- TooltipProvider globally for micro-explanations

Internationalization (i18n)
- i18next + react-i18next configured in `src/i18n.ts`
- Languages bundled: English (en), Hindi (hi), Telugu (te), Odia (or), Bengali (bn)
- Language persistence via `localStorage` and dynamic `lang` attribute updates

Responsive & Mobile UX
- Utility layer adds mobile ergonomics: `.mobile-*` classes for text sizing, spacing, layout, break-words
- Prevents iOS zoom on input focus (16px rule)
- Drawer/panel patterns (`.mobile-drawer`, `.mobile-control-panel`) for small screens

Icons & Symbols
- `lucide-react` provides consistent, crisp line icons aligned with the forest/administrative theme
- Status colors map to tokens: approved (green), pending (amber), rejected (red)

Performance & DX
- Vite dev server, SWC React plugin, TypeScript strictness
- Shadcn codegen aligned with `components.json` aliases and Tailwind config
- Assets served from `public`, geospatial JSON data colocated for local demos

How to Extend
- Add themed components by referencing HSL CSS variables; never hardcode colors
- Prefer shadcn primitives for consistency and accessibility
- When adding routes, wrap with `ProtectedRoute` as needed and consider role mapping in `RoleBasedRouter`
- For new languages, drop `translation.json` under `src/locales/<lng>` and register in `src/i18n.ts`

File Pointers
- Theme and utilities: `src/index.css`, `tailwind.config.ts`
- App shell and routing: `src/App.tsx`, `src/main.tsx`
- Components: `src/components`, `src/components/ui`
- Pages: `src/pages`
- i18n: `src/i18n.ts`, `src/locales/*/translation.json`
- Icons: `lucide-react`
- Maps: `react-leaflet` + Leaflet styles in `index.css`
